{"info": {"author": "SergeyMatveev88", "author_email": "dazranagon@yandex.ru", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Framework :: Django", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# drf-dx-datagrid\n# Overview\nThis package provides easy integration between [Django REST framework](https://www.django-rest-framework.org) and [DevExtreme Data Grid](https://js.devexpress.com/Demos/WidgetsGallery/Demo/DataGrid/Overview/jQuery/Light/)\n\nInstall drf-dx-datagrid, replace classname ModelViewSet to DxModelViewSet in your django project and it will support devextreme load options and will return a JSON structure that is fully compatible with what Data Grid expects.\nIt handles grouping, paging, filtering and ordering on serverside.\n\n# Configuration\nDefine your ModelViewSet classes as on this example:\n```python\nfrom drf_dx_datagrid import DxModelViewSet\n\nclass MyModelViewSet(DxModelViewSet):\n    serializer_class = MyModelSerializer\n    queryset = core.models.MyModel.objects.all()\n```\nJS example:\n```js\nimport CustomStore from 'devextreme/data/custom_store';\nimport axios from \"axios\";\n\nexport const getUpsStore = (my_url, customStoreOptions) => {\n    const load = (loadOptions) => {\n        return axios(`${my_url}`, {\n                params: loadOptions\n            }\n        ).then((response) => response.data\n        )\n    };\n    return new CustomStore({...customStoreOptions, load: load});\n}\n```    \n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/SergeyMatveev88/drf-dx-datagrid", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "drf-dx-datagrid", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/drf-dx-datagrid/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/drf-dx-datagrid/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/SergeyMatveev88/drf-dx-datagrid"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/drf-dx-datagrid/0.1/", "requires_dist": ["djangorestframework"], "requires_python": ">=3.5", "summary": "This package provides easy integration between Django REST framework and DevExtreme Data Grid", "version": "0.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>drf-dx-datagrid</h1>\n<h1>Overview</h1>\n<p>This package provides easy integration between <a href=\"https://www.django-rest-framework.org\" rel=\"nofollow\">Django REST framework</a> and <a href=\"https://js.devexpress.com/Demos/WidgetsGallery/Demo/DataGrid/Overview/jQuery/Light/\" rel=\"nofollow\">DevExtreme Data Grid</a></p>\n<p>Install drf-dx-datagrid, replace classname ModelViewSet to DxModelViewSet in your django project and it will support devextreme load options and will return a JSON structure that is fully compatible with what Data Grid expects.\nIt handles grouping, paging, filtering and ordering on serverside.</p>\n<h1>Configuration</h1>\n<p>Define your ModelViewSet classes as on this example:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">drf_dx_datagrid</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">DxModelViewSet</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">class</span> <span class=\"nc\">MyModelViewSet</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">DxModelViewSet</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">serializer_class</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">MyModelSerializer</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">queryset</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">core</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">models</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">MyModel</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">objects</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">all</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</pre>\n<p>JS example:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kr\">import</span> <span class=\"nx\">CustomStore</span> <span class=\"nx\">from</span> <span class=\"s1\">'devextreme/data/custom_store'</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"kr\">import</span> <span class=\"nx\">axios</span> <span class=\"nx\">from</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"axios\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"kr\">export</span> <span class=\"kr\">const</span> <span class=\"nx\">getUpsStore</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">my_url</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nx\">customStoreOptions</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"p\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"kr\">const</span> <span class=\"nx\">load</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">loadOptions</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"p\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"k\">return</span> <span class=\"nx\">axios</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"sb\">`</span><span class=\"si\">${</span><span class=\"nx\">my_url</span><span class=\"si\">}</span><span class=\"sb\">`</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n                <span class=\"nx\">params</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"nx\">loadOptions</span>\n            <span class=\"p\">}</span>\n        <span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"nx\">then</span><span class=\"p\">((</span><span class=\"nx\">response</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"p\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"nx\">response</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">data</span>\n        <span class=\"p\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">return</span> <span class=\"k\">new</span> <span class=\"nx\">CustomStore</span><span class=\"p\">({...</span><span class=\"nx\">customStoreOptions</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nx\">load</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"nx\">load</span><span class=\"p\">});</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6570918, "releases": {"0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "956ecf462a3eee5c823b7d68ec5e532b", "sha256": "2aa62c0ea0587766ba0b2f0c33dc745ecadf5423a2364033c209bff61b95a410"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "drf_dx_datagrid-0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "956ecf462a3eee5c823b7d68ec5e532b", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.5", "size": 6124, "upload_time": "2020-02-04T19:31:38", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-04T19:31:38.209473Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/a1/05/a585ed7b909da43e2488162946e924a2f87c04230fad96aa99179bbcb2d9/drf_dx_datagrid-0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "c6595712a9c2d9f319ec8c30a1b780fe", "sha256": "76d2d17f0bb1784a5100d435c60bd2c809aabd17d01bb138ddda3cdd119925ca"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "drf_dx_datagrid-0.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "c6595712a9c2d9f319ec8c30a1b780fe", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.5", "size": 4098, "upload_time": "2020-02-04T19:31:40", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-04T19:31:40.185686Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/e4/06/ac0b94102a44b0707343a0d49be526267248ae1e38a67b571e63bfe83ed6/drf_dx_datagrid-0.1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}]}, "urls": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "956ecf462a3eee5c823b7d68ec5e532b", "sha256": "2aa62c0ea0587766ba0b2f0c33dc745ecadf5423a2364033c209bff61b95a410"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "drf_dx_datagrid-0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "956ecf462a3eee5c823b7d68ec5e532b", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.5", "size": 6124, "upload_time": "2020-02-04T19:31:38", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-04T19:31:38.209473Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/a1/05/a585ed7b909da43e2488162946e924a2f87c04230fad96aa9